## Definition of Done

### Story Level
- All acceptance criteria from the ticket are met
- Tests written and passing for new functionality
- Code compiles with no type errors (tsc --noEmit passes)
- Commit messages follow conventional commit format with ticket ID
- PR created with description linking to the Jira ticket
- If acceptance criteria are already met, report this — do not make unnecessary changes

### Epic Level
- All child stories complete
- Integration tests pass across story boundaries
- No regressions in existing test suite

### Feature Level
- All child epics complete
- End-to-end tests pass
- Documentation updated if applicable

## Working Conventions
- Read existing code before making changes
- Run tests before committing
- Keep changes focused on the ticket scope
- Use conventional commits (feat:, fix:, chore:, docs:)
- Do NOT commit `claude-progress.txt` — it is a session scratchpad and must stay in `.gitignore`
- If acceptance criteria are already met by existing code, state this clearly in your output — the system will verify and close the ticket without a PR
